+# EXPERIMENT: Validating First-Order Euler Integration in DiffBot's Hardware Interface
+
+## 1. System Under Test
+
+The integration step lives in `example_2/hardware/diffbot_system.cpp`, inside
+`DiffBotSystemHardware::read()`:
+
+```cpp
+// diffbot_system.cpp:192
+hw_positions_[i] = hw_positions_[i] + period.seconds() * hw_velocities_[i];
+```
+
+`write()` (`diffbot_system.cpp:215`) mirrors the command into the state velocity
+without filtering or delay:
+
+```cpp
+hw_velocities_[i] = hw_commands_[i];
+```
+
+Therefore the wheel-joint position state is the discrete-time integral of the
+commanded wheel velocity, sampled by the controller manager at `update_rate`.
+
+Relevant fixed parameters from `example_2/bringup/config/diffbot_controllers.yaml`:
+
+| Parameter | Value | Source |
+|-----------|-------|--------|
+| `controller_manager.update_rate` | `10 Hz` (Δt_nominal = 0.1 s) | line 3 |
+| `diffbot_base_controller` type | `diff_drive_controller/DiffDriveController` | line 9 |
+| `wheel_radius` | `0.015 m` | line 18 |
+| `wheel_separation` | `0.10 m` | line 16 |
+| `linear.x.max_acceleration` | `1.0 m/s²` (ramp confound) | line 44 |
+| `cmd_vel_timeout` | `0.5 s` | line 33 |
+| `publish_rate` (odom) | `50 Hz` | line 24 |
+| `open_loop` | `true` | line 30 |
+
+The default launch (`example_2/bringup/launch/diffbot.launch.py`) uses
+`use_mock_hardware:=false`, which loads the `DiffBotSystemHardware` plugin —
+i.e. the integrator under test. We launch with this default.
+
+The two joints exposed are `left_wheel_joint` and `right_wheel_joint`
+(`example_2/description/ros2_control/diffbot.ros2_control.xacro:21,26`), each
+with one velocity command interface and `position`+`velocity` state interfaces.
+
+## 2. Hypothesis (Falsifiable)
+
+**H1 (per-step):** Let `p[k]` and `v[k]` be the wheel-joint position and velocity
+state samples at the k-th `read()` call, and `Δt[k] = t[k+1] − t[k]` the cycle
+period passed to `read()`. Then for every k:
+
+```
+p[k+1] − p[k] − Δt[k] · v[k] = 0   (within IEEE-754 double rounding, |ε| ≤ 1e-12)
+```
+
+**H2 (windowed integral):** For any analysis window `[t_a, t_b]` over which the
+recorded wheel-joint velocity state is constant at value `v_w`,
+
+```
+Δp_meas := p(t_b) − p(t_a)   ≈   v_w · (t_b − t_a)
+```
+
+with absolute error bounded by
+
+```
+|Δp_meas − v_w · (t_b − t_a)|  ≤  |v_w| · Δt_nominal  =  |v_w| · 0.1 s.
+```
+
+The bound follows because the only Euler-quantization error is the at-most-one-step
+mismatch between the analysis window edges and the discrete `read()` grid; v_w is
+constant inside, so internal samples telescope exactly.
+
+**Refutation criteria.** The hypothesis is refuted if:
+- H1 residuals systematically exceed `1e-9 rad` (six orders of magnitude above
+  IEEE-754 noise) on more than 1 % of cycles, OR
+- H2 windowed error exceeds `|v_w| · 0.1 s` on any condition where v_w is verified
+  constant for ≥ 5 s, OR
+- Δp_meas vs. (v_w · T) regression slope deviates from 1 by more than 1 % across
+  the velocity sweep.
+
+## 3. Independent Variables
+
+| Variable | Levels | Rationale |
+|----------|--------|-----------|
+| Commanded chassis linear velocity `v_cmd` on `/cmd_vel.linear.x` | `0.005`, `0.010`, `0.015 m/s` (→ wheel ω = 0.333, 0.667, 1.000 rad/s via ω = v/r) | Spans an order of magnitude of integrand magnitude; max value keeps wheel ω at 1 rad/s, well below any limit. |
+| Hold duration `T` after ramp settles | `5 s`, `10 s`, `20 s` | Tests that error does not grow with T (Euler is unbiased here). |
+| Sign | `+v_cmd`, `−v_cmd` | Symmetry check; rules out asymmetric sign bugs. |
+
+A full factorial gives 3 × 3 × 2 = 18 trials. Each trial is repeated 3 times
+(N=54 total), with the entire ROS 2 stack relaunched between trials (see §6, FM3).
+
+`/cmd_vel.angular.z = 0` for all trials so both wheels receive identical
+commands and serve as independent replicates.
+
+## 4. Confounds Held Constant
+
+| Confound | Control |
+|----------|---------|
+| DiffDriveController acceleration ramp (1.0 m/s²) | Not removed; instead, exclude all samples before the ramp settles. Settle detection: first sample where `|v_state − v_target| < 1e-4 rad/s` for 3 consecutive samples. Discard an additional 0.5 s buffer. Largest level (`v_cmd = 0.015 m/s`) ramps in ≈ 15 ms, so settling cost is negligible vs. T. |
+| Update rate | Do NOT edit `diffbot_controllers.yaml`. Verify post-hoc that recorded `/joint_states` timestamp deltas have median ≈ 0.1 s. |
+| `cmd_vel_timeout = 0.5 s` | Republish `/cmd_vel` at 10 Hz for the entire hold window, well below timeout. |
+| Initial state | NaN-guarded init in `on_activate` (`diffbot_system.cpp:148-156`) only zeros position if NaN. Cold-launch the stack each trial to guarantee `p(0) = 0`. |
+| Wall-clock vs. ROS time | Use `/joint_states.header.stamp` (ROS time) for all integration; never use `rclcpp::Clock::now()` post-hoc. |
+| Other publishers writing to `/cmd_vel` | Confirm no RViz teleop or joystick is running (`ros2 topic info /cmd_vel` should show exactly one publisher: our test driver). |
+| RViz CPU load | Launch with `gui:=false` to avoid non-deterministic load on the executor. |
+
+## 5. Data to Record
+
+Use `ros2 bag record -o trial_<id>.bag` started **before** publishing any
+`/cmd_vel` and stopped **after** the final hold ends. Topics:
+
+| Topic | Type | Native rate | Why |
+|-------|------|-------------|-----|
+| `/joint_states` | `sensor_msgs/JointState` | 10 Hz (paced by `update_rate`, published by `joint_state_broadcaster`) | **Primary.** `position[i]` and `velocity[i]` are exactly the values being asserted on. |
+| `/cmd_vel` | `geometry_msgs/Twist` | 10 Hz (driver) | Marks intended step edges for windowing; lets us verify the controller actually saw the step. |
+| `/diffbot_base_controller/odom` | `nav_msgs/Odometry` | 50 Hz | Independent cross-check via `open_loop` integration in the controller; should agree on the integrated wheel angle within controller numerics. |
+| `/dynamic_joint_states` | `control_msgs/DynamicJointState` | 10 Hz | Carries the same state interface values published by the broadcaster, useful as a redundant source. |
+| `/rosout` | log | event-driven | Captures the throttled `RCLCPP_INFO_THROTTLE` lines from `read()`/`write()` (`diffbot_system.cpp:200,220`) as a sanity stream. |
+
+We do not record `/tf`. We need wheel-joint integration only, not chassis pose.
+
+## 6. Procedure (Self-Contained)
+
+Prerequisites: ROS 2 (any release supported by this repo), this workspace built
+and sourced (`colcon build --packages-up-to ros2_control_demo_example_2`).
+
+For each of the 54 trials:
+
+1. **Cold start the stack** in terminal A (kills prior `controller_manager`):
+   ```
+   ros2 launch ros2_control_demo_example_2 diffbot.launch.py gui:=false
+   ```
+   Wait for `Successfully activated!` from the DiffBot logger.
+
+2. **Verify steady state** in terminal B:
+   ```
+   ros2 topic echo --once /joint_states
+   ```
+   Both `position` entries must be 0.0 (NaN-guarded init; non-zero indicates
+   a hot relaunch — abort and retry).
+
+3. **Start recording** in terminal C, before sending any command:
+   ```
+   ros2 bag record -o trial_<id>.bag /joint_states /cmd_vel \
+       /diffbot_base_controller/odom /dynamic_joint_states /rosout
+   ```
+
+4. **Drive a constant `/cmd_vel`** in terminal D, at 10 Hz for `T + 1 s` seconds
+   (the +1 s gives buffer for the ramp), then stop:
+   ```
+   ros2 topic pub -r 10 /cmd_vel geometry_msgs/Twist \
+       "{linear: {x: <v_cmd>}, angular: {z: 0.0}}"
+   ```
+   Use Ctrl-C at exactly `T + 1 s`.
+
+5. **Stop recording** (Ctrl-C in terminal C), **shut down the stack** (Ctrl-C in
+   terminal A). Confirm both processes exit before next trial.
+
+6. Record the trial parameters (`v_cmd`, `T`, sign, repeat index) in
+   `trials.csv` alongside the bag path.
+
+## 7. Analysis
+
+For each bag:
+
+1. Load `/joint_states` into a per-joint table `(t_k, p_k, v_k)`.
+2. Compute `Δt_k = t_{k+1} − t_k`; verify `median(Δt) ∈ [0.099, 0.101] s`.
+3. **H1 test:** compute residual `r_k = p_{k+1} − p_k − Δt_k · v_k` for every k.
+   Pass if `max(|r_k|) ≤ 1e-9` and `99 %ile(|r_k|) ≤ 1e-12`.
+4. **H2 test:** locate the steady window:
+   - Find first index `k_a` where `v_k` is within `1e-4 rad/s` of the target
+     wheel velocity for 3 consecutive samples; advance by 5 samples (0.5 s buffer).
+   - Find last index `k_b` while `/cmd_vel` is still being published.
+   - Compute `Δp_meas = p_{k_b} − p_{k_a}`, `Δp_pred = mean(v_{k_a..k_b}) · (t_{k_b} − t_{k_a})`.
+   - Pass if `|Δp_meas − Δp_pred| ≤ |v_w| · 0.1 s`.
+5. **Aggregate regression:** across all 54 trials, regress `Δp_meas` on
+   `Δp_pred`. Pass if slope ∈ [0.99, 1.01], intercept |·| < 1e-3 rad,
+   R² > 0.9999.
+
+## 8. Visualization Plan
+
+Four figures, generated from the bags:
+
+1. **`fig_timeseries.pdf`** — for one representative trial (`v_cmd = 0.010 m/s`,
+   `T = 10 s`, left wheel): three stacked subplots vs. ROS time:
+   (a) `v_state` (state velocity from `/joint_states`) and `v_target = v_cmd / r`
+   overlaid — inspect the ramp settling against our detection threshold;
+   (b) `p_state` overlaid with the offline-recomputed cumulative-Euler curve
+   `p_pred[k] = Σ Δt_j · v_j` — curves must visually coincide;
+   (c) `cmd_vel.linear.x` step trace, to mark the analysis window edges.
+
+2. **`fig_per_step_residual.pdf`** — scatter of `r_k` (H1 residual) vs. time
+   for all trials, log-scaled |y|. Inspect for: (i) any drift with time
+   (would indicate a bias term beyond Euler); (ii) any spikes correlated with
+   ramp transitions; (iii) overall magnitude vs. the 1e-9 ceiling.
+
+3. **`fig_predicted_vs_measured.pdf`** — scatter of `Δp_meas` vs. `Δp_pred` for
+   all 54 trials, color-coded by `v_cmd`, marker shape by sign, with the y=x
+   line and the ±|v_w|·0.1 s envelope shaded. Inspect for: deviation from y=x,
+   asymmetry between positive/negative signs, T-dependent fanning.
+
+4. **`fig_period_histogram.pdf`** — histogram of `Δt_k` across all trials,
+   with vertical line at the nominal 0.1 s. Inspect that jitter is small
+   compared to T and that no samples are dropped (no cluster near 0.2 s).
+
+## 9. Failure Modes and Mitigations
+
+1. **Acceleration ramp contaminates the window.** The DiffDriveController
+   limits acceleration to 1.0 m/s² (`diffbot_controllers.yaml:44`), so the
+   commanded wheel velocity ramps in over `v_cmd / 1.0` seconds. If we naively
+   take `t_a` at the cmd_vel rising edge, Δp_meas will fall short of v_w·T by
+   roughly half a ramp's worth of integral. **Mitigation:** detect ramp
+   completion programmatically from `/joint_states.velocity[i]` (threshold
+   `1e-4 rad/s` for 3 consecutive samples plus a 0.5 s buffer) instead of
+   trusting the cmd_vel edge; equivalently, use `v_w := mean(v_state)` over the
+   window, not the externally commanded value.
+
+2. **Joint-state broadcaster aliasing the read() grid.** `read()` updates
+   positions at 10 Hz; `joint_state_broadcaster` also runs at 10 Hz inside the
+   same `controller_manager` executor. If the broadcaster is one cycle out of
+   phase, our `(p_k, v_k)` pair may correspond to the state *before* that
+   cycle's `read()`, breaking the expected H1 identity by a one-step shift.
+   **Mitigation:** allow a one-sample alignment offset in H1 — test both
+   `r_k = p_{k+1} − p_k − Δt_k · v_k` and `r_k = p_{k+1} − p_k − Δt_k · v_{k+1}`
+   and report which holds. This distinguishes "Euler is wrong" from "samples
+   are off-by-one in the same direction every time".
+
+3. **State not zeroed at trial start (hot relaunch).** `on_activate`
+   (`diffbot_system.cpp:148-156`) only resets to zero `if (std::isnan(...))`.
+   On a soft re-activate without process restart, position carries over.
+   **Mitigation:** kill the entire `ros2_control_node` between trials (full
+   `Ctrl-C` of the launch file) and verify Step 2 of the procedure shows
+   `position == 0.0`; abort the trial otherwise. Also analysis uses
+   `Δp = p_{k_b} − p_{k_a}`, which is invariant to a non-zero starting offset.
+
+4. **`cmd_vel_timeout` triggers mid-trial.** If our publisher pauses for
+   > 0.5 s, the controller drops to zero, breaking the constant-v assumption.
+   **Mitigation:** the publisher in Step 4 runs at `-r 10` (10 Hz), 5× the
+   timeout margin; additionally, post-hoc we verify the recorded `/cmd_vel`
+   inter-message gap stays below 0.2 s for the entire window and reject the
+   trial if not.
+
+5. **Update-rate jitter not bounded by Δt_nominal.** Under load, the
+   controller_manager loop may overrun, producing `period.seconds()` larger
+   than 0.1 s. The H2 bound `|v_w|·0.1 s` then under-estimates the true
+   quantization error. **Mitigation:** in analysis, replace the bound with
+   `|v_w| · max(Δt_k)` using the actually observed periods, and report both.
+   If `max(Δt) > 0.15 s`, mark the trial as load-contaminated and rerun on
+   a quieter machine (or with `gui:=false` if RViz was inadvertently on).
